The paper discusses a new statistical machine learning paradigm for multi-label learning, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The use of semantic codes to represent labels is similar to the approach used in zero-shot learning, which is relevant to cs.CV and cs.AI. The practical applications mentioned in the abstract, such as image tagging and article categorization, suggest relevance to cs.CL and cs.IR. Finally, the validation of the approach using a PAC bound suggests relevance to cs.LG. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.IR.
